♪ Hey, hey, hey,

02:20.502 --> 02:22.584
hey, hey, Jessie ♪

02:26.334 --> 02:28.000
My fortune says,

02:28.042 --> 02:29.126
"You will be blessed

02:29.127 --> 02:30.209
with many children."

02:30.250 --> 02:31.451
- I don't know
- about blessed.

02:34.209 --> 02:36.438
Mine says I have

02:36.439 --> 02:38.667
a large sum of money

02:34.209 --> 02:38.667
coming my way.

02:38.709 --> 02:40.110
- Did something
- happen to Grandma?

02:41.083 --> 02:42.418
Try to at least

02:42.419 --> 02:43.751
sound concerned.

02:43.792 --> 02:45.210
Ooh, I'm going to be

02:45.211 --> 02:46.626
on a magazine cover!

02:46.667 --> 02:48.042
That's your fortune?

02:48.083 --> 02:49.250
- No, I just got
- an email.

02:50.792 --> 02:52.375
- All right, who
- stole my hair?

02:52.417 --> 02:54.209
- Father Time?
- Mother Nature?

02:55.709 --> 02:58.042
No, I mean my toupee.

02:58.083 --> 02:59.459
- I already lost
- my hair once.

02:59.500 --> 03:01.209
I can't lose it again!

03:01.250 --> 03:02.751
- Can't you get
- a new one?

03:02.792 --> 03:03.959
Something more

03:03.960 --> 03:05.125
Brad Pitt, less armpit?

03:06.500 --> 03:08.334
- No, it was
- custom made.

03:08.375 --> 03:10.042
- My concert's
- in a few hours,

03:10.083 --> 03:11.355
And "the Hair" can't be

03:11.356 --> 03:12.626
the only guy in the band

03:12.667 --> 03:14.167
without any hair!

03:14.209 --> 03:16.059
- Don't worry, Bertram.
- I'll help you find it.

03:16.083 --> 03:17.083
It'll be perfect practice

03:17.084 --> 03:18.084
for my audition.

03:18.125 --> 03:19.250
I'm up for the role

03:19.251 --> 03:20.375
of Detective Phyllis Marlowe

03:20.417 --> 03:22.167
- in a film noir
- TV commercial.

03:22.209 --> 03:24.042
- We know. You've been
- making us watch

03:24.083 --> 03:25.188
All those 1940s

03:25.189 --> 03:26.292
mystery movies.

03:26.334 --> 03:28.043
The mystery is how

03:28.044 --> 03:29.751
we stayed awake.

03:29.792 --> 03:31.189
And why everyone

03:31.190 --> 03:32.584
talked so weird

03:29.792 --> 03:32.584
back then?

03:32.626 --> 03:34.250
- They sounded
- totes cray.

03:36.667 --> 03:38.042
- So, what's the
- commercial for?

03:38.083 --> 03:39.105
Oh, Legs Up

03:39.106 --> 03:40.125
Bug Spray.

03:40.167 --> 03:42.087
- But it's only - gonna air in
- Foreign markets.

03:42.125 --> 03:43.584
Because it was

03:43.585 --> 03:45.042
just banned in

03:42.125 --> 03:45.042
the United States.

03:45.083 --> 03:46.418
Hey, it was supposed

03:46.419 --> 03:47.751
to kill roaches,

03:45.083 --> 03:47.751
and it did.

03:47.792 --> 03:49.125
- It just
- didn't stop there.

03:53.500 --> 03:55.000
So, blondie, do you have

03:55.001 --> 03:56.500
anything you'd like

03:53.500 --> 03:56.500
to tell me?

03:56.542 --> 03:57.834
Yeah. You're dressing

03:57.835 --> 03:59.125
for the wrong century.

04:00.876 --> 04:02.834
- And why are you talking
- like a silent movie?

04:02.876 --> 04:04.293
Nobody talks

04:04.294 --> 04:05.709
in silent mo...

04:02.876 --> 04:05.709
Oh, never mind.

04:07.626 --> 04:08.897
I am in character.

04:08.898 --> 04:10.167
It helps me think.

04:10.209 --> 04:11.355
So, why do you assume

04:11.356 --> 04:12.500
I took the toupee?

04:12.542 --> 04:13.689
Because I found

04:13.690 --> 04:14.834
glittery footprints

04:14.876 --> 04:16.500
- leading up to
- Bertram's room,

04:16.541 --> 04:18.059
- A flake of your - nail polish on
- The wig stand,

04:18.083 --> 04:19.147
And your nameplate

04:19.148 --> 04:20.209
necklace at the scene

04:18.083 --> 04:20.209
of the crime!

04:20.250 --> 04:22.041
- (SCOFFS) That's all
- you've got?

04:22.083 --> 04:23.375
No.

04:23.417 --> 04:24.730
I also found this

04:24.731 --> 04:26.042
lock of golden hair.

04:26.083 --> 04:27.083
That's not mine!

04:27.125 --> 04:28.876
- Good thing, because
- it's dry, brittle,

04:28.918 --> 04:30.751
- And has horrible
- split ends.

04:30.792 --> 04:32.083
How dare you!

04:32.125 --> 04:33.459
I just had

04:33.460 --> 04:34.792
a hydrating treatment!

04:34.834 --> 04:35.980
So it is yours!

04:35.981 --> 04:37.125
Tell me everything

04:34.834 --> 04:37.125
you know.

04:37.167 --> 04:38.768
- Including the name
- of that treatment.

04:40.083 --> 04:41.792
- I was only
- trying to help!

04:41.834 --> 04:42.834
I couldn't let Bertram

04:42.835 --> 04:43.834
wear that wig

04:41.834 --> 04:43.834
the way it was.

04:43.876 --> 04:45.560
- So, I decided - to give it
- A makeover...

04:45.584 --> 04:47.252
JESSIE: And just like that,

04:47.253 --> 04:48.918
she sang like a canary.

04:48.959 --> 04:50.751
- Emma Ross
- was a snazzy dame.

04:50.792 --> 04:52.393
- She knew that if
- being ugly were a crime,

04:52.417 --> 04:54.338
- That toupee would go
- straight to the slammer.

04:55.167 --> 04:56.167
Ow!

04:59.083 --> 05:02.042
Oh, that's better.

05:02.083 --> 05:03.727
- JESSIE: She was - only trying to help
- The help,

05:03.751 --> 05:04.793
Who was up coif creek

05:04.794 --> 05:05.834
without a comb.

05:05.876 --> 05:07.459
- So she tried
- some conditioner,

05:07.500 --> 05:08.959
And it might've worked,

05:09.000 --> 05:10.105
except this wasn't

05:10.106 --> 05:11.209
your run-of-the-mill mop.

05:11.250 --> 05:13.167
No!

05:13.209 --> 05:14.918
Why would

05:14.919 --> 05:16.626
the big palooka

05:13.209 --> 05:16.626
buy such cheap hair?

05:16.667 --> 05:17.959
We really should

05:17.960 --> 05:19.250
give the poor,

05:16.667 --> 05:19.250
sweet lug a raise.

05:21.876 --> 05:22.918
Well, that's better.

05:24.876 --> 05:26.185
- I didn't know - the toupee
- Would react

05:26.209 --> 05:27.959
- To my conditioner
- like that!

05:28.000 --> 05:29.143
- I can't believe
- Bertram planned

05:29.167 --> 05:30.792
- To make a comeback
- in synthetic hair!

05:32.500 --> 05:34.000
- The man does love
- his coupons.

05:36.083 --> 05:37.375
- So where's
- the toupee?

05:37.417 --> 05:39.209
- I hid it in the
- living room cabinet.

05:39.250 --> 05:41.042
- Where we keep
- the school supplies?

05:41.083 --> 05:42.647
Brilliant! No one

05:42.648 --> 05:44.209
would ever suspect you

05:41.083 --> 05:44.209
of opening that.

05:44.250 --> 05:45.334
(CHUCKLES)

05:45.335 --> 05:46.417
I know, right?

05:46.459 --> 05:47.792
- But when I
- went back later

05:47.834 --> 05:49.459
- To see if the toupee
- had de-puffed,

05:49.500 --> 05:50.584
It was gone!

05:53.500 --> 05:54.918
Wait!

05:54.959 --> 05:56.500
- I know who has
- the toupee!

05:56.542 --> 05:58.500
- It was in the
- school supply cabinet,

05:58.542 --> 05:59.813
And the only person who

05:59.814 --> 06:01.083
does schoolwork around here

05:58.542 --> 06:01.083
is Ravi!

06:01.125 --> 06:02.604
(GASPS)

06:02.605 --> 06:04.083
Of course!

06:04.125 --> 06:05.522
So, who has

06:05.523 --> 06:06.918
the toupee?

06:06.959 --> 06:08.251
We should use

06:08.252 --> 06:09.542
your college fund

06:06.959 --> 06:09.542
on a nice vacation.

06:15.584 --> 06:17.584
Bertram?

06:17.626 --> 06:18.834
You're supposed to be

06:18.835 --> 06:20.042
on stage in Central Park

06:17.626 --> 06:20.042
in three hours.

06:20.083 --> 06:21.272
Are you rehearsing

06:21.273 --> 06:22.459
any dance steps besides

06:22.500 --> 06:23.709
the Sitting Man?

06:25.042 --> 06:26.521
I can't do my moves

06:26.522 --> 06:28.000
without my hair.

06:28.042 --> 06:29.082
- I have nothing
- to flip.

06:31.209 --> 06:32.626
You dance

06:32.627 --> 06:34.042
with your feet,

06:31.209 --> 06:34.042
not your follicles.

06:34.083 --> 06:35.143
- C'mon, show me
- what you got.

06:35.167 --> 06:36.393
- I'll give you
- some pointers.

06:36.417 --> 06:37.709
Well, in case

06:37.710 --> 06:39.000
Jessie does find

06:36.417 --> 06:39.000
my toupee,

06:39.042 --> 06:40.521
I guess I should be

06:40.522 --> 06:42.000
ready to dazzle them

06:42.042 --> 06:44.125
with my high-energy funk.

06:46.500 --> 06:48.000
Help me up.

06:53.042 --> 06:55.959
(DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)

