Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

07:12.042 --> 07:13.042
(BONES CRACKING)

07:16.209 --> 07:17.584
Wow.

07:17.626 --> 07:19.500
That was great!

07:19.542 --> 07:20.689
But maybe you could do it

07:20.690 --> 07:21.834
a little more like this.

07:33.167 --> 07:34.647
- If I had my hair,
- I could do that.

07:36.459 --> 07:38.000
Really?

07:38.042 --> 07:39.292
- So it had
- magical powers?

07:43.876 --> 07:45.226
- Okay, there's no need
- to be nervous.

07:45.250 --> 07:46.351
- I'm just going to
- ask you a few...

07:46.375 --> 07:49.042
I am guilty!

07:49.083 --> 07:50.813
Send me to my room until

07:50.814 --> 07:52.542
college entrance exams!

07:52.584 --> 07:54.250
- Okay, I appreciate
- your honesty,

07:54.292 --> 07:55.730
But you confessing so quick

07:55.731 --> 07:57.167
really takes the fun

07:54.292 --> 07:57.167
out of this for me.

07:58.250 --> 07:59.272
Oh, I apologize,

07:59.273 --> 08:00.292
Jessie.

08:00.334 --> 08:01.375
- Shall I
- resist more?

08:01.417 --> 08:03.375
- Oh, just tell me
- what you know.

08:03.417 --> 08:06.058
- This girdle's really tight, - and
I have to go - To the bathroom.

08:07.250 --> 08:09.147
It was a classic case

08:09.148 --> 08:11.042
of being in the wrong place

08:07.250 --> 08:11.042
at the wrong time.

08:11.083 --> 08:13.250
- I had just color-coordinated
- my kurta closet...

08:13.292 --> 08:14.646
JESSIE: Ravi folded faster

08:14.647 --> 08:16.000
than a dry cleaner

08:13.292 --> 08:16.000
at quittin' time.

08:17.459 --> 08:19.000
- The poor crumb
- found the toupee

08:19.042 --> 08:20.251
While pilfering recreational

08:20.252 --> 08:21.459
homework supplies.

08:21.500 --> 08:23.000
- Even his crimes
- were boring.

08:24.459 --> 08:25.647
What is this

08:25.648 --> 08:26.834
puzzling puffball?

08:26.876 --> 08:28.417
(CROAKING)

08:28.459 --> 08:30.043
You are right!

08:30.044 --> 08:31.626
It is Bertram's toupee!

08:31.667 --> 08:33.042
We must fix this.

08:33.082 --> 08:34.708
(CROAKING)

08:34.751 --> 08:37.000
Fine, I will fix it.

08:37.042 --> 08:38.251
You know, it would not

08:38.251 --> 08:39.458
kill you to lift a claw

08:37.042 --> 08:39.458
around here once in a while.

08:39.500 --> 08:40.751
(CROAKING)

08:42.333 --> 08:43.934
- JESSIE: Ravi wanted
- to return the toupee,

08:43.958 --> 08:45.001
But he knew if Bertram

08:45.002 --> 08:46.042
took a gander at it now,

08:46.083 --> 08:47.522
it would take him

08:47.523 --> 08:48.959
on a one-way trip

08:46.083 --> 08:48.959
over Breakdown Falls.

08:51.083 --> 08:52.083
(EXPLODING)

08:54.083 --> 08:56.042
Huzzah! Success!

08:56.083 --> 08:57.292
(SNIFFING) Oh!

08:57.334 --> 08:58.834
(COUGHING)

08:58.876 --> 09:00.084
Dear gods! Mrs. Kipling,

09:00.085 --> 09:01.292
do you smell that?

09:04.667 --> 09:06.209
- I will take that
- as a yes.

09:07.709 --> 09:09.167
JESSIE: Ravi had no choice

09:09.209 --> 09:10.376
but to take the noxious

09:10.377 --> 09:11.542
noggin warmer to...

09:11.584 --> 09:13.459
The Fixer.

09:13.500 --> 09:14.709
(CAR SWERVING AND CRASHING)

09:14.751 --> 09:16.042
Aw, lemons!

09:16.083 --> 09:17.542
(CAR HONKING)

09:17.584 --> 09:18.709
Are you

09:18.710 --> 09:19.834
the Fixer?

09:19.876 --> 09:21.000
- Who wants
- to know?

09:22.083 --> 09:23.959
- I do.
- That is why I asked.

09:25.083 --> 09:26.876
- How'd you
- get up here?

09:26.918 --> 09:28.230
Remind me to have

09:28.231 --> 09:29.542
my doorman rubbed out,

09:29.584 --> 09:30.584
and I don't mean

09:30.585 --> 09:31.585
by a masseuse.

09:32.959 --> 09:34.126
Miss Fixer,

09:34.127 --> 09:35.292
I need your help.

09:35.334 --> 09:36.501
I am desperate

09:36.502 --> 09:37.667
to get this

09:35.334 --> 09:37.667
problem fixed.

09:37.709 --> 09:39.584
- So why are you twistin'
- my nose about it?

09:39.626 --> 09:40.834
Because your nickname

09:40.835 --> 09:42.042
and your business card

09:42.083 --> 09:43.397
rather strongly imply

09:43.398 --> 09:44.709
that you fix things.

09:44.751 --> 09:46.209
(SNIFFING) Oh!

09:46.250 --> 09:47.750
Yeah, but that thing stinks

09:47.751 --> 09:49.250
like last week's chop suey.

09:50.083 --> 09:51.209
Perhaps this

09:51.210 --> 09:52.334
will help?

09:58.042 --> 10:00.042
Deal. Now beat it,

10:00.083 --> 10:01.563
unless you want to

10:01.564 --> 10:03.042
stick around for

10:00.083 --> 10:03.042
a knuckle sandwich.

10:03.083 --> 10:04.918
- No, thank you.
- I just ate.

10:06.375 --> 10:08.334
(KNUCKLES CRACKING)

10:08.375 --> 10:10.001
Oh, I get it.

10:10.002 --> 10:11.626
That was a threat,

10:08.375 --> 10:11.626
not a menu item.

10:13.083 --> 10:14.083
(SNIFFING) Oh!

10:16.083 --> 10:17.313
So Zuri

10:17.314 --> 10:18.542
has the toupee?

10:16.083 --> 10:18.542
Yes.

10:18.584 --> 10:20.375
- And all of my
- vacation money.

10:20.417 --> 10:21.709
- Which, let us
- face it,

10:21.751 --> 10:23.751
- I was probably going to use
- for college anyway.

10:27.459 --> 10:29.834
(DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)

10:32.500 --> 10:34.417
- (GROANING)
- This is hopeless!

10:34.459 --> 10:35.751
Bertram, the problem

10:35.752 --> 10:37.042
isn't your dancing,

10:34.459 --> 10:37.042
it's your attitude.

10:37.083 --> 10:38.959
And also your dancing.

10:40.542 --> 10:41.793
You have to show

10:41.794 --> 10:43.042
some confidence

10:40.542 --> 10:43.042
on stage.

10:43.083 --> 10:44.626
Think of your fans.

10:44.667 --> 10:46.518
- This performance - is the highlight
- Of their lives,

10:46.542 --> 10:47.772
Which I have to assume

10:47.773 --> 10:49.000
are profoundly empty.

10:50.500 --> 10:51.543
But they're expecting

10:51.544 --> 10:52.584
"the Hair,"

10:52.626 --> 10:54.000
not "the Scalp."

10:54.042 --> 10:55.476
- Well then, maybe you could
- have a different nickname.

10:55.500 --> 10:57.042
Like what?

10:57.083 --> 10:58.251
Like...

10:58.252 --> 10:59.417
"The Hoarder!"

10:57.083 --> 10:59.417
Or "the Napper."

10:59.459 --> 11:00.876
- Oh! Oh!
- How about

11:00.918 --> 11:02.480
"the One with

11:02.481 --> 11:04.042
an Unhealthy Obsession

11:00.918 --> 11:04.042
for Nesting Dolls"?

11:04.083 --> 11:05.876
- That won't fit
- on a T-shirt!

11:07.167 --> 11:09.042
- Maybe you
- could be...

11:09.083 --> 11:10.751
- "The Hat"?
- Yeah!

11:10.792 --> 11:12.459
We had "the Hat."

11:12.460 --> 11:14.125
He quit the band!

11:14.167 --> 11:16.083
- You know nothing
- about Badd Direction!

11:20.792 --> 11:22.125
Hey, all I did was

11:22.167 --> 11:23.314
take the toupee

11:23.315 --> 11:24.459
and get the smell out,

11:24.500 --> 11:26.042
- just like
- Ravi wanted.

11:26.083 --> 11:27.583
That's a relief.

11:27.584 --> 11:29.083
I knew you were a good kid...

11:29.125 --> 11:31.086
- Despite what - Kenny Chesney's
- Bodyguard says.

11:32.834 --> 11:34.500
- So, where's
- the toupee?

11:34.542 --> 11:35.542
Up a tree.

11:35.584 --> 11:37.042
- Please tell me
- that's a metaphor.

11:37.083 --> 11:38.459
Nope. See, I tried

11:38.460 --> 11:39.834
to wash it,

11:39.876 --> 11:41.230
but that did not

11:41.231 --> 11:42.584
go so well.

11:39.876 --> 11:42.584
I was just following...

11:42.626 --> 11:44.126
JESSIE: Everyone knew

11:44.127 --> 11:45.626
the Fixer had

11:42.626 --> 11:45.626
many skills,

11:45.667 --> 11:47.417
- but laundry
- wasn't one of them.

11:48.167 --> 11:50.125
Aw, nuts!

11:50.167 --> 11:52.042
(BLOWING)

11:52.083 --> 11:53.397
Maybe five bottles

11:53.398 --> 11:54.709
of bubble bath

11:52.083 --> 11:54.709
was too much.

11:54.751 --> 11:55.876
(SNIFFING)

11:55.918 --> 11:56.918
Smells beautiful,

11:56.919 --> 11:57.919
though.

11:59.209 --> 12:01.167
- JESSIE: The Fixer
- may have nixed the stink...

12:01.209 --> 12:02.626
(BIRD CAWING)

12:02.627 --> 12:04.042
but she was about to

12:01.209 --> 12:04.042
eat crow.

12:04.083 --> 12:05.542
Hey!

12:05.584 --> 12:07.876
This job is for the birds!

12:13.751 --> 12:14.814
So, let me see

12:14.815 --> 12:15.876
if I follow your tune.

12:15.918 --> 12:17.480
Some sticky-taloned

12:17.481 --> 12:19.042
Maltese falcon air-lifted

12:15.918 --> 12:19.042
the wacky weave

12:19.083 --> 12:20.397
to tall, green, and

12:20.398 --> 12:21.709
leafy over here?

12:21.751 --> 12:23.897
If you have an English

12:23.898 --> 12:26.042
button, please push it!

12:26.083 --> 12:27.751
- Sorry, but
- I am paying $100

12:27.792 --> 12:29.226
- For a dialogue coach for
- a 30-second commercial.

12:29.250 --> 12:30.543
I gotta get

12:30.544 --> 12:31.834
my money's worth.

12:31.876 --> 12:33.542
- Now, are you sure
- you saw the bird

12:33.584 --> 12:35.500
- Bring Bertram's toupee
- to this tree?

12:35.542 --> 12:37.396
Definitely. I watched

12:37.397 --> 12:39.250
the whole thing

12:35.542 --> 12:39.250
through the telescope.

12:39.292 --> 12:41.042
- Well, there's
- no hairpiece up here.

12:41.083 --> 12:42.542
Just some binoculars,

12:42.543 --> 12:44.000
and alarmingly large eggs.

12:45.918 --> 12:46.980
(CAWING)

12:46.981 --> 12:48.042
(GASPS)

12:45.918 --> 12:48.042
No! No!

12:48.083 --> 12:49.584
- JESSIE: Take that,
- stupid bird!

12:49.626 --> 12:50.626
(GRUNTING)

12:54.083 --> 12:55.667
- My belt is stuck
- on the branch.

12:55.709 --> 12:57.542
- (LAUGHING)
- (CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

12:57.584 --> 12:58.606
Wait, these

12:58.607 --> 12:59.626
are Luke's and...

12:59.667 --> 13:01.042
I know this tree.

13:01.083 --> 13:02.647
Zuri, you said the bird

13:02.648 --> 13:04.209
snatched the toupee

13:01.083 --> 13:04.209
at 4:15?

13:04.250 --> 13:05.709
Yeah, why?

13:05.751 --> 13:07.709
- Because this is
- where Luke sits

13:07.751 --> 13:08.959
To watch the 4:00 p.m.

13:08.960 --> 13:10.167
Ladies Trampoline Practice.

13:10.209 --> 13:11.897
He must've been up here

13:11.898 --> 13:13.584
when the bird snatched

13:10.209 --> 13:13.584
the toup to its coop.

13:13.626 --> 13:15.209
- Thank you,
- Dr. Seuss.

13:16.167 --> 13:18.042
- (CAWING)
- Oh, no!

13:18.083 --> 13:19.147
He's coming back! Help me!

13:19.148 --> 13:20.209
Get me down, quick!

13:26.626 --> 13:28.167
What? You said "quick."

13:32.209 --> 13:35.042
♪ I'm burned but I am free

13:35.083 --> 13:36.605
♪ No more grill marks

13:36.606 --> 13:38.125
on my heart ♪

13:41.083 --> 13:42.563
So, what do you think

13:42.564 --> 13:44.042
of our hit music video?

13:44.083 --> 13:45.709
- I think people
- must not have had

13:45.751 --> 13:47.397
A lot of entertainment

13:47.398 --> 13:49.042
options back then.

13:45.751 --> 13:49.042
(SIGHING)

13:49.083 --> 13:50.334
Okay, we've all

13:50.335 --> 13:51.584
seen Bertram's...

13:52.083 --> 13:54.042
Talents.

13:54.083 --> 13:55.444
- So now let's
- help him rehearse.

13:56.667 --> 13:58.626
- Thanks, but
- I'm not going on.

13:58.667 --> 13:59.834
I don't want to be

13:59.835 --> 14:01.000
the only one up there

13:58.667 --> 14:01.000
with no hair.

14:01.042 --> 14:02.667
- Hey, don't think
- about that.

14:02.709 --> 14:04.231
Just remember

14:04.232 --> 14:05.751
you have great hair...

14:07.125 --> 14:08.876
On the inside.

14:10.083 --> 14:11.563
I'm sure in your warped mind

14:11.564 --> 14:13.042
that was encouraging.

14:14.125 --> 14:15.918
- Okay, I'll give it
- a go.

14:15.959 --> 14:17.021
But just like when

14:17.022 --> 14:18.083
I tried skinny jeans,

14:18.125 --> 14:19.480
I don't think

14:19.481 --> 14:20.834
this is gonna work.

14:20.876 --> 14:22.252
At least this time

14:22.253 --> 14:23.626
we won't have to use

14:20.876 --> 14:23.626
the Jaws of Life!

14:25.292 --> 14:26.501
Why can I not be

14:26.502 --> 14:27.709
the cool one?

14:27.751 --> 14:29.834
Genetics.

14:29.876 --> 14:31.292
- But don't
- feel bad.

14:31.334 --> 14:33.334
- Luke will never - read a book
- Without pictures.

14:34.334 --> 14:36.042
- Okay, ready?
- And...

14:36.083 --> 14:37.583
Five, six,

14:37.584 --> 14:39.083
seven, eight.

14:39.125 --> 14:40.584
♪ First time I saw you

14:40.585 --> 14:42.042
on the street

14:42.083 --> 14:43.667
♪ You looked at me... ♪

14:43.709 --> 14:44.375
- I don't know
- about this...

14:44.417 --> 14:46.292
- C'mon, what could
- go wrong?

14:47.292 --> 14:49.250
(ALL MOANING)

14:51.959 --> 14:53.334
What happened here?

14:53.375 --> 14:54.729
All I know is we started

14:54.730 --> 14:56.083
cabbage patching.

14:56.125 --> 14:57.876
The rest is a blur.

14:59.250 --> 15:00.611
- Here, Luke,
- let me help you up.

15:01.083 --> 15:02.209
Thank you.

15:02.250 --> 15:03.501
A-ha! Look at

15:03.502 --> 15:04.751
your arm!

15:02.250 --> 15:04.751
I know...

15:04.792 --> 15:07.042
I've been working out.

15:07.083 --> 15:08.083
No, I mean,

15:08.084 --> 15:09.084
look at these scratches.

15:09.125 --> 15:11.042
- You got these
- in the nest!

15:11.083 --> 15:12.083
- You have
- the toupee!

15:12.918 --> 15:14.042
Hang on...

15:14.083 --> 15:15.727
- All this time you were
- trying to convince me

15:15.751 --> 15:17.334
- I can get by
- without my hair,

15:17.375 --> 15:18.792
- And it was you
- who stole it?

15:18.834 --> 15:20.125
- Hey, wait,
- I can explain.

15:20.167 --> 15:22.042
- So Luke took
- the toupee?

15:22.083 --> 15:23.209
I'm glad I'm not

15:23.210 --> 15:24.334
the only one.

15:24.375 --> 15:26.167
- Wait a minute,
- you stole it too?

15:26.209 --> 15:27.272
Actually,

15:27.273 --> 15:28.334
Luke didn't steal it.

15:28.375 --> 15:29.542
- He took it
- from a bird,

15:29.584 --> 15:31.268
- Who stole it from Zuri,
- who got it from Ravi,

15:31.292 --> 15:32.393
- Who found it
- where Emma hid it,

15:32.417 --> 15:34.334
- After she took it
- from you. Ha!

15:34.959 --> 15:36.250
Man, I'm good!

15:36.292 --> 15:37.834
- I'm gonna sell
- so much bug spray.

15:39.125 --> 15:40.792
- Okay, so
- I took it!

15:40.834 --> 15:42.418
But what was I

15:42.419 --> 15:44.000
supposed to do,

15:40.834 --> 15:44.000
leave it in that tree?

15:44.042 --> 15:45.063
I was trying to do

15:45.064 --> 15:46.083
Bertram a favor.

15:46.125 --> 15:47.209
See, Melinda had just done

15:47.210 --> 15:48.292
a double backflip,

15:48.334 --> 15:49.834
- when I noticed
- the toupee.

15:52.459 --> 15:53.938
JESSIE: Luke started yammering

15:53.939 --> 15:55.417
that the toupee was

15:52.459 --> 15:55.417
in bad shape

15:55.459 --> 15:57.042
- because he had to
- wrestle it away

15:57.083 --> 15:59.042
- From a pterodactyl
- with a temper.

15:59.083 --> 16:01.042
- I haven't seen
- this many feathers

16:01.083 --> 16:02.209
Since I got tangled up

16:02.210 --> 16:03.334
in that kick line

16:01.083 --> 16:03.334
at the Cotton Club!

16:05.334 --> 16:06.688
JESSIE: He didn't want

16:06.689 --> 16:08.042
to get caught

16:05.334 --> 16:08.042
holding the rug,

16:08.083 --> 16:09.792
- but before
- he could fix it...

16:09.834 --> 16:11.334
(BERTRAM HUMMING)

16:15.083 --> 16:17.042
Hey, Bertie!

16:17.083 --> 16:18.810
- What brings you
- into this neck of the woods?

16:18.834 --> 16:20.313
My job,

16:20.314 --> 16:21.792
unfortunately.

16:23.083 --> 16:24.459
Oh, cheer up, bub.

16:24.500 --> 16:25.668
The Great Depression

16:25.669 --> 16:26.834
is over.

16:26.876 --> 16:28.459
- You haven't seen
- my paycheck.

16:29.375 --> 16:30.375
Out!

16:36.209 --> 16:37.230
I meant to go back

16:37.231 --> 16:38.250
and get the toupee

16:36.209 --> 16:38.250
cleaned up,

16:38.292 --> 16:39.563
but I've been so busy

16:39.564 --> 16:40.834
helping Bertram

16:38.292 --> 16:40.834
with his choreography,

16:40.876 --> 16:42.167
- I totally
- forgot about it.

16:42.209 --> 16:43.584
How could you forget

16:43.585 --> 16:44.959
you had my toupee?

16:45.000 --> 16:46.188
All day I've been talking

16:46.189 --> 16:47.375
about how much I need it.

16:47.417 --> 16:48.939
In my defense,

16:48.940 --> 16:50.459
your dancing

16:47.417 --> 16:50.459
is very distracting.

16:52.083 --> 16:53.230
Okay, so apparently

16:53.231 --> 16:54.375
everyone's guilty.

16:54.417 --> 16:55.730
First thing tomorrow,

16:55.731 --> 16:57.042
I'll issue a mass grounding.

16:57.083 --> 16:58.560
- But for now, - the important
- Thing is

16:58.584 --> 16:59.834
- We know where
- the toupee is!

16:59.876 --> 17:01.042
- It's in
- the freezer!

17:01.083 --> 17:02.480
Well, an icy toupee

17:02.481 --> 17:03.876
is fine with me!

17:03.918 --> 17:04.939
It'll thaw out

17:04.940 --> 17:05.959
before my first

17:03.918 --> 17:05.959
pop 'n lock.

17:08.000 --> 17:09.460
Is he talking about

17:09.461 --> 17:10.917
his dance moves,

17:08.000 --> 17:10.917
or his joints?

17:13.459 --> 17:15.041
I don't see it!

17:15.083 --> 17:16.584
- There it is!
- My toupee?

17:16.626 --> 17:17.834
No, but I solved

17:17.835 --> 17:19.041
the mystery of

17:16.626 --> 17:19.041
the missing remote.

17:19.083 --> 17:20.250
Yay!

17:26.541 --> 17:27.935
- Now, I'm not trying
- to accuse anyone,

17:27.959 --> 17:29.268
- But one of you
- has the toupee.

17:29.292 --> 17:31.042
- Jessie, I do not mean
- to pick nits,

17:31.083 --> 17:32.272
But that is

17:32.273 --> 17:33.459
a textbook example

17:31.083 --> 17:33.459
of an accusation.

17:35.083 --> 17:36.272
Now, listen here.

17:36.273 --> 17:37.459
You were all

17:35.083 --> 17:37.459
in on the grift.

17:37.500 --> 17:39.022
You're all hoodlums, punks,

17:39.023 --> 17:40.542
goons, flimflam artists...

17:40.584 --> 17:42.042
- If she keeps
- talking like this,

17:42.083 --> 17:43.500
I'm calling a doctor.

17:45.083 --> 17:46.251
Cram it,

17:46.252 --> 17:47.417
Jeeves!

17:47.459 --> 17:48.501
It's her process.

17:48.502 --> 17:49.542
Just go with it.

17:51.083 --> 17:53.209
- Now, whoever took that toupee
- out of the freezer

17:53.250 --> 17:54.585
And isn't coming clean

17:54.586 --> 17:55.918
is the lowest of the low.

17:55.959 --> 17:57.250
(CROAKING)

17:57.292 --> 17:58.542
Can it, Kippy.

18:00.417 --> 18:01.459
Perhaps Mrs. Kipling

18:01.460 --> 18:02.500
is hungry.

18:02.542 --> 18:04.293
She can't be. I just gave her

18:04.294 --> 18:06.042
some grub. Two frozen rats.

18:06.083 --> 18:07.542
(CROAKING)

18:07.584 --> 18:09.959
Really? Then that means

18:10.000 --> 18:11.000
you were the last one

18:11.001 --> 18:12.001
in the freezer, Jessie.

18:12.042 --> 18:13.542
And that's where

18:13.543 --> 18:15.042
the toupee was last seen...

18:15.083 --> 18:16.542
Wait, you guys think

18:16.543 --> 18:18.000
I pinched the rug?

18:18.042 --> 18:19.459
- That's a bunch
- of hooey!

18:19.500 --> 18:21.185
- I never touched it, see,
- and I'll prove it to you.

18:21.209 --> 18:22.667
Here's what happened...

18:22.709 --> 18:23.917
JESSIE: Rat wrangling

18:23.918 --> 18:25.125
was never my favorite chore...

18:25.167 --> 18:27.584
Still, this dame was game.

18:29.083 --> 18:30.522
I gave a hungry lizard

18:30.523 --> 18:31.959
her chow, and that's all

18:29.083 --> 18:31.959
she wrote.

18:32.000 --> 18:34.042
- Anyone who thinks
- I took Bertram's toupee is...

18:34.083 --> 18:35.083
(RECORD SCRATCHING)

18:39.083 --> 18:40.375
Ugh.

18:41.542 --> 18:42.959
- There's a rat
- in this story,

18:43.000 --> 18:44.022
And it's not

18:44.023 --> 18:45.042
the one Kipling ate!

18:45.083 --> 18:46.834
You fed Bertram's toupee

18:46.835 --> 18:48.584
to Mrs. Kipling?

18:48.626 --> 18:50.292
- It was an
- honest mistake!

18:50.334 --> 18:52.292
- I didn't mean to mess up
- the toupee!

18:52.334 --> 18:54.042
We messed it up.

18:54.083 --> 18:55.209
You destroyed it.

18:55.250 --> 18:56.647
And you call yourself

18:56.648 --> 18:58.042
a fake detective.

18:58.083 --> 18:59.724
- Hey, I'm the one
- who solved the crime!

18:59.751 --> 19:01.167
- You committed
- the crime!

19:01.209 --> 19:02.643
- I'm pretty sure - those cancel
- Each other out!

19:02.667 --> 19:03.855
No, no...

19:03.856 --> 19:05.042
(ALL ARGUING)

19:05.083 --> 19:06.563
Stop it! You were all

19:06.564 --> 19:08.042
involved in this.

19:08.083 --> 19:09.355
And thanks to you,

19:09.356 --> 19:10.626
my reunion concert

19:08.083 --> 19:10.626
is ruined!

19:12.459 --> 19:13.730
Nanny,

19:13.731 --> 19:15.000
ground thyself.

19:19.500 --> 19:21.000
Hey, Bertram.

19:21.042 --> 19:23.042
- I'm sorry I fed
- your toupee to the lizard.

19:23.083 --> 19:24.397
I tried to find a card

19:24.398 --> 19:25.709
for that, but no such luck.

19:27.083 --> 19:28.397
It's okay. You didn't know

19:28.398 --> 19:29.709
what you were doing.

19:29.751 --> 19:31.311
- Which is kind of
- par for the course.

19:33.083 --> 19:34.751
Look, Bertram,

19:34.792 --> 19:36.084
I really think

19:36.085 --> 19:37.375
you should perform

19:34.792 --> 19:37.375
with Badd Direction.

19:37.417 --> 19:38.522
You've waited

19:38.523 --> 19:39.626
25 years for this!

19:39.667 --> 19:41.355
I can't. Not without

19:41.356 --> 19:43.042
my secret weapon.

19:43.083 --> 19:44.230
Well, I've only known you

19:44.231 --> 19:45.375
without your hair, and...

19:45.417 --> 19:47.167
- I think
- you're wonderful.

19:47.209 --> 19:48.334
I mean, think of all

19:48.335 --> 19:49.459
the things you're good at.

19:49.500 --> 19:51.083
- Like what?
- Well, you can...

19:51.125 --> 19:52.709
Huh?

19:52.751 --> 19:54.375
- And there's...
- Uh...

19:54.417 --> 19:56.042
(CHUCKLING)

19:56.083 --> 19:58.000
- Let's not get - bogged down
- In the details.

19:58.792 --> 20:00.417
The point is,

20:00.459 --> 20:01.543
every single one

20:01.544 --> 20:02.626
of those kids

20:00.459 --> 20:02.626
went out of their way

20:02.667 --> 20:04.459
- to make sure you
- looked great tonight.

20:04.500 --> 20:06.083
- I mean, Zuri did
- laundry for you.

20:06.125 --> 20:07.250
(CHUCKLES)

20:07.251 --> 20:08.375
That was sweet.

20:08.417 --> 20:10.458
- By the way, - the new machine's
- Coming tomorrow.

20:13.792 --> 20:14.918
Look, we all

20:14.919 --> 20:16.042
believe in you, Bertram.

20:16.083 --> 20:17.334
- Really?
- LUKE: Really.

20:18.292 --> 20:19.334
(GASPS)

20:19.375 --> 20:20.375
Aww...

20:22.083 --> 20:23.500
(CHUCKLES)

20:23.542 --> 20:24.793
We are your

20:24.794 --> 20:26.042
secret weapon.

20:26.083 --> 20:27.042
- And we'll be
- rooting for you

20:27.083 --> 20:28.751
- When you are up
- on that stage tonight,

20:28.792 --> 20:30.185
- Showing everyone
- why you still get

20:30.209 --> 20:32.042
- Free fish
- in Finland.

20:32.083 --> 20:32.834
(LAUGHS)

20:32.876 --> 20:34.209
- I appreciate it, guys,
- but...

20:34.250 --> 20:35.272
No, no, no.

20:35.273 --> 20:36.292
No buts.

20:36.334 --> 20:37.834
- Now you get up
- on that stage

20:37.876 --> 20:39.685
- And you give those - fans what they've
- Been waiting for.

20:39.709 --> 20:41.626
- Their social security
- checks?

20:43.250 --> 20:45.042
No!

20:45.083 --> 20:46.792
- Badd Direction
- has a new direction,

20:46.834 --> 20:48.313
And it's bigger,

20:48.314 --> 20:49.792
better, and bald!

20:49.834 --> 20:51.751
You're right! I'm going

20:51.752 --> 20:53.667
to go out there

20:49.834 --> 20:53.667
and give it my all!

20:53.709 --> 20:55.375
- I just hope they don't
- laugh at me.

20:55.417 --> 20:56.459
Of course

20:56.460 --> 20:57.500
they won't

20:55.417 --> 20:57.500
laugh at you!

20:57.542 --> 20:59.001
They paid $65 to see

20:59.002 --> 21:00.459
some middle-aged

20:57.542 --> 21:00.459
one-hit wonders.

21:00.500 --> 21:02.301
- They have no business
- laughing at anybody.

